[normal]5.1 General destinations
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.1.1 
[normal]Tables 3a and 3b show the 
[normal]main destinations of male and female graduates
[normal] in the computer and engineering sciences
[normal]. The
[normal] majority of students enter some form of employment, with a 
[normal]relatively 
[normal]small
[normal] proportion 
[normal]entering further study
[normal]. This trend differs from the physical, biological and mathematical sciences where higher proportions of students enter further study (around one third
[normal] of physical science graduates, both male and female, u
[normal]ndertake further study
[normal],
[normal] for example)
[normal]. As the tables show, there is some fluctuation in the trends over the period considered but the proportions of m
[normal]en and women at each stage tend
[normal] to be reasonably similar.  
